    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter the second most recent commit #c4b658fe (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31112), my cursor jumps to the very top after opening a file and inserting a character.\n\nNot reproducible without any plugins but reproducible with only nvim-cmp (https://github.com/hrsh7th/nvim-cmp).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Have nvim-cmp (https://github.com/hrsh7th/nvim-cmp) installed with minimal config (only buffer completion).\n2. Checkout commit  #c4b658fe or later.\n3. Build neovim.\n4. Run `nvim foo.bar`\n5. Enter insert-mode in a spot different than 1:1 and insert a character.\n6. notice the cursor jumping to 0:0 immediately.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect the cursor to not jump randomly.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-c4b658fed\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.12.8-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty and ghostty, does not seem to matter\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nInitially nvim-git from AUR and now reproduced from source manually.",
